Nyamira Governor John Nyagarama's son has passed on. Ndemo Nyagarama died at the Nairobi Hospital on Monday after a long struggle with menengitis. A close family member said they received the news with shock, especially coming at a time the governor is also hospitalised in the US. The county boss has been away for almost a month with the county under the stewardship of deputy governor Amos Nyaribo. "He could not breathe with ease and has been complaining of chest pains. The situation was not good at all. Let him rest in peace," the family member, who asked not to be named, said. Click here for the latest political news